Date:2/19/2004 3:40:53 PM
From:Spekulatius
Amoezzi - re TCN, TSU and TND
TSU and TND are "twins" very similar balance sheets, valuation and prospects
and balance sheet quality. I am sticking with TSU because of its slightly
higher growth and better liquidity. The stocks are closely correlated which may
come in handy - if TSU turns south (more) I may just take the ST loss and
switch to TND for tax reasons.

TCN is cheaper per P/S number than both TND and TSU but it has much weaker
fundamentals in terms of balance sheet (debt) and earnings. So TND and TSU are
more conservative and TCN is more speculative, IMO. the issue that I have with
TCN is that their balance sheet is still weak even though its improving. TCN is
FCF positive but only because they are not investing - they continue to operate
the outdate TDMA network while competitors are upgrading to CDMA and GSM
rapidly. this is the reason why TCN is loosing market share. If TCN starts to
upgrade to GSM or CDMA their FCF will turn negative unless they can improve
their profit margin considerably. I do note that yahoo has a forward P/E of 8
for TCN but I do not know what this estimate is based upon, it looks very
optimistic to me.

They are fighting against better capitalized competitors with better networks
and are loosing market share, that's the reason why they are so cheap. If they
can continue to turn around the stock should outperform TSU and TND, if
fundamentals turn for the worse, they will be a marginal player operating with
outdated hardware. But sure the TCN's chart looks better, especially today.

FWIW, I added to my entry position in TSU today.
