%BOM---------------------
Date:2/20/2004 11:58:30 PM
From:James Clarke
<<Can anyone help me to find out: How to estimate a
risk to reward ratio for going long on a stock trade.
A appreciate all the advice.>>

Understand the business and understand the financial statements enough to value
the business. Then understand what the current price vs. the intrinsic value
and the risk inherent in the business implies about the odds of losing money on
the investment. I know of no other way to do this. Shortcuts don't work, though
there are plenty of them.

If you're thinking of "going long a stock trade" you're not in the right frame
of mind. Think of "buying a business" and what that means.
%EOM----------------------

