From:Mark Marcellus
Have you ever looked at the NAIC's Stock Study Guide (SSG)? It's pretty basic,
but it's a great starting point, and there's one section that estimates up side
vs. down side potential based on historical P/E ranges and future earnings
forecasts.

I started using SSG's in 1989 when I first began investing on my own. I look at
a lot more now than I did then, but the SSG is still the first thing I do when
I begin evaluating a company.
