From:Grommit
yield & grt-g

Another reit preferred started trading last week: grt-g. These seem to start
trading close to issue price, then move to a premium. I expect that to continue
as long as interest rates don't climb too much. This one yields 7.9% ($2.03 div
/ $25.50 price). However if redeemed in 2009 at $25, the effective yield is
7.6%.

I expect the price to quickly (30 days) move to $26.4 to make the yield in line
with other preferred shares -- again, unless overall rates rise. I'll take the
3.5% gain if it occurs. But I'll hold this for awhile since this investment
replaces other preferreds which were selling at premiums.

PS
I posted here about grt-f last septmeber, when it started trading and the price
was under $24.88. Now the price is $26.8 (effective yield 6.7%).

